allowance(address,address).details: Returns the amount of tokens that an owner has allowed a spender to spend.

params.owner: The address that owns the tokens.
params.spender: The address that is allowed to spend the tokens.

returns._0: The amount of tokens allowed to be spent.

approve(address,uint256).details: Approves the specified address to spend the specified amount of tokens on behalf of the message sender.

params.spender: The address to approve for spending the tokens.
params.value: The amount of tokens to be spent.

returns._0: True if the approval was successful, revert otherwise.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the balance of the specified address.

params.account: The address to query the balance of.

returns._0: The balance of the specified address.

constructor.details: Constructor to initialize the ERC20 token.

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfers tokens from the sender to the specified recipient.

params.to: The address to transfer tokens to.
params.value: The amount of tokens to transfer.

returns._0: True if the transfer was successful, revert otherwise.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers tokens from one address to another.

params.from: The address to transfer tokens from.
params.to: The address to transfer tokens to.
params.value: The amount of tokens to transfer.

returns._0: True if the transfer was successful, revert otherwise.

allowance(address,address).details: Returns the amount of tokens that an owner has allowed a spender to spend.

params.owner: The address that owns the tokens.
params.spender: The address that is allowed to spend the tokens.

returns._0: The amount of tokens allowed to be spent.

approve(address,uint256).details: Approves the specified address to spend the specified amount of tokens on behalf of the message sender.

params.spender: The address to approve for spending the tokens.
params.value: The amount of tokens to be spent.

returns._0: True if the approval was successful, revert otherwise.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the balance of the specified address.

params.account: The address to query the balance of.

returns._0: The balance of the specified address.

burn().details: Allows the admin to burn all remaining tokens.

returns._0: True if the burn was successful.

constructor.details: Constructor to initialize the SurvivalCoin token.

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfers tokens from the sender to the specified recipient.

params.to: The address to transfer tokens to.
params.value: The amount of tokens to transfer.

returns._0: True if the transfer was successful, revert otherwise.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers tokens from one address to another.

params.from: The address to transfer tokens from.
params.to: The address to transfer tokens to.
params.value: The amount of tokens to transfer.

returns._0: True if the transfer was successful, revert otherwise.

changeDepositAddress(address).details: Allows the admin to change the deposit address.

constructor.details: Constructor to initialize the SurvivalCoin ICO.

params._hardCap: The hard cap of the ICO.
params._saleStart: The start time of the ICO.
params._tokenPrice: The price of one token in Ether.
params._tokenTradeStart: The start time for token trading.

getCurrentState().details: Returns the current state of the ICO.

halt().details: Allows the admin to halt the ICO.

investTokens().details: Allows external callers to invest in the ICO.

resume().details: Allows the admin to resume the ICO.
